diseases.Name: herpes zoster
diseases.Definition: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection located_in nerve fiber, has_material_basis_in Human herpesvirus 3, which reactivates after appearing as chickenpox in childhood. The virus is transmitted_by direct contact with the rash, which can develop into chickenpox in newly-infected individuals. The infection has_symptom rash which is followed by blisters, has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, has_symptom malaise, has_symptom itching, has_symptom burning pain, and has_symptom paresthesia.

diseases.Name: lymphatic system disease
diseases.Definition: An immune system disease that is located_in the lymphatic system.

diseases.Name: bladder carcinoma
diseases.Definition: A urinary bladder cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from epithelial cells.

diseases.Name: renal cell carcinoma
diseases.Definition: A renal carcinoma that has_material_basis_in the lining of the proximal convoluted renal tubule of the kidney.

diseases.Name: physical disorder
diseases.Definition: A disease that has_material_basis_in a genetic abnormality, error with embryonic development, infection or compromised intrauterine environment.

diseases.Name: sensory system disease
diseases.Definition: A nervous system disease which is located in a part of the nervous system responsible for processing sensory information that consists of sensory receptors, neural pathways, and parts of the brain involved in sensory perception. Commonly recognized sensory systems are those for vision, hearing, somatic sensation (touch), taste and olfaction (smell).

diseases.Name: endocrine system disease
diseases.Definition: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in endocrine glands which secretes a type of hormone directly into the bloodstream to regulate the body.

diseases.Name: adrenal gland disease
diseases.Definition: An endocrine system disease that is located_in the adrenal gland.

diseases.Name: lung carcinoma
diseases.Definition: A lung cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from epithelial cells and is located_in the lungs and has_symptom cough and has_symptom chest discomfort or pain and has_symptom weight loss and has_symptom hemoptysis.

diseases.Name: oral cavity cancer
diseases.Definition: A gastrointestinal system cancer that is located_in the oral cavity.

diseases.Name: carbohydrate metabolic disorder
diseases.Definition: An inherited metabolic disorder that affect the catabolism and anabolism of carbohydrates.

diseases.Name: endometrial cancer
diseases.Definition: A uterine cancer that is located_in tissues lining the uterus.

diseases.Name: integumentary system cancer
diseases.Definition: An organ system cancer that is located_in the skin, hair and nails.

diseases.Name: bone disease
diseases.Definition: A connective tissue disease that affects the structure or development of bone or causes an impairment of normal bone function.

diseases.Name: large intestine cancer
diseases.Definition: An intestinal cancer that effects the long, tube-like organ that is connected to the small intestine at one end and the anus at the other.

diseases.Name: leukopenia
diseases.Definition: A leukocyte disorder that is characterized by a decrease in the number of white blood cells (leukocytes) found in the blood, which places individuals at increased risk of infection.

diseases.Name: pituitary gland disease
diseases.Definition: An endocrine system disease that is located_in the pituitary gland.

diseases.Name: primary ovarian insufficiency
diseases.Definition: An ovarian disease where ovaries do not produce estrogen despite high levels of circulating gonadotropins in women under 40.

diseases.Name: type 2 diabetes mellitus
diseases.Definition: A diabetes mellitus that is characterized by high blood sugar, insulin resistance, and relative lack of insulin.

diseases.Name: malaria
diseases.Definition: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease characterized as a vector-borne infectious disease caused by the presence of protozoan parasites of the genus Plasmodium in the red blood cells, transmitted from an infected to an uninfected individual by the bite of anopheline mosquitoes, and characterized by periodic attacks of chills and fever that coincide with mass destruction of blood cells and the release of toxic substances by the parasite at the end of each reproductive cycle.

diseases.Name: peripheral nerve sheath neoplasm
diseases.Definition: A peripheral nervous system neoplasm that is located in the connective tissue surrounding nerves.

diseases.Name: adrenal medulla cancer
diseases.Definition: An adrenal gland cancer that is located_in the adrenal medulla.

diseases.Name: nervous system disease
diseases.Definition: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the central nervous system or located_in the peripheral nervous system.

diseases.Name: childhood B-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia
diseases.Definition: A childhood acute lymphoblastic leukemia that has_material_basis in B-cells.

diseases.Name: hepatitis B
diseases.Definition: A viral infectious disease that results_in inflammation located_in liver, has_material_basis_in Hepatitis B virus, which is transmitted_by sexual contact, blood transfusions, or fomites like needles or syringes. The infection has_symptom fever, fatigue, loss of appetite, nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, clay-colored bowel movements, joint pain, and jaundice.

diseases.Name: hair disease
diseases.Definition: An integumentary system disease that is located_in hair.

diseases.Name: Ohdo syndrome
diseases.Definition: A syndrome that is characterized by blepharophimosis, ptosis, dental hypoplasia, hearing impairment and intellectual disability.

diseases.Name: intestinal disease
diseases.Definition: A gastrointestinal system disease that is located_in the intestine.

diseases.Name: chromosomal disease
diseases.Definition: A genetic disease that has_material_basis_in extra, missing, or re-arranged chromosomes.

diseases.Name: uterine cancer
diseases.Definition: A female reproductive organ cancer that is located_in the uterus.

diseases.Name: biliary tract cancer
diseases.Definition: A hepatobiliary system cancer that results_in malignant growth located_in the gallbladder or located_in the bile duct.

diseases.Name: gastrointestinal system cancer
diseases.Definition: An organ system cancer located_in gastrointestinal tract that is manifested in organs of the gastrointestinal system.

diseases.Name: allergic disease
diseases.Definition: An immune system disease that is an exaggerated immune response to allergens, such as insect venom, dust mites, pollen, pet dander, drugs or some foods.

diseases.Name: nephritis
diseases.Definition: A kidney disease that is characterized by an inflammation of the kidneys.

diseases.Name: thyroid gland carcinoma
diseases.Definition: A thyroid gland cancer that has_material_basis_in epithelial cells.

diseases.Name: head and neck squamous cell carcinoma
diseases.Definition: A head and neck carcinoma that has_material_basis_in squamous cells that line the moist, mucosal surfaces inside the head and neck.

diseases.Name: artery disease
diseases.Definition: A vascular disease that is located_in an artery.

diseases.Name: seasonal affective disorder
diseases.Definition: A mental depression that involves presentation of depressive symptoms only during a specific season of the year.

diseases.Name: blindness
diseases.Definition: An eye disease characterized by a lack or loss of vision.

diseases.Name: autosomal genetic disease
diseases.Definition: A monogenic disease that has_material_basis_in a mutation in a single gene on one of the non-sex chromosomes.

diseases.Name: myelodysplastic syndrome
diseases.Definition: A bone marrow cancer that is characterized by under production of white blood cells, red blood cells and platelets.

diseases.Name: respiratory system disease
diseases.Definition: A disease of anatomical entity that located_in the respiratory system which extends from the nasal sinuses to the diaphragm.

diseases.Name: high grade glioma
diseases.Definition: A cell type cancer that has_material_basis_in glial cells and is located in brain or located in spine.

diseases.Name: substance-related disorder
diseases.Definition: A disease of mental health involving the abuse or dependence on a substance that is ingested in order to produce a high, alter one's senses, or otherwise affect functioning.

diseases.Name: pervasive developmental disorder
diseases.Definition: A developmental disorder of mental health that refers to a group of five disorders characterized by impairments in socialization and communication, as well as restricted interests and repetitive behaviors.

diseases.Name: urinary bladder cancer
diseases.Definition: An urinary system cancer that results_in malignant growth located_in the urinary bladder.
